SIMPLE: refit
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Refit
<hw>Re*fit"</hw> <pr>(r?*f?t")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To fit or prepare for use again; to repair; to restore after damage
or decay; <as>as, to <ex>refit</ex> a garment; to <ex>refit</ex> ships
of war.</as></def> <rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To fit out or supply a second time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Refit</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Refit
<hw>Re*fit"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To obtain repairs or supplies;
<as>as, the fleet returned to <ex>refit</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Refitment</ent>⟦br⟧
